          "date": "2012-05-17 07:34:18.000000000",
          "tz": 540
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Keith Mannthey",
          "email": "keith.mannthey@intel.com",
          "date": "2013-01-12 02:12:04.000000000",
          "tz": -480
        },
        "subject": "LU-1391 lov: Hold LOV ref count until target OSCs are released",
        "message": "LU-1391 lov: Hold LOV ref count until target OSCs are released\n\nWhen LOV obd_device on a client node is registered with target OSCs\nas observer, LOV obd_refcount isn't incremented at the time.\nThus, there is a possibility that obd_observer could be freed while\nstill be referred, like in obd_nitify_observer().\n\nThis patch increments/decrements LOV obd_refcount with\nobd_register/unregister_observer_with_osc() when LOV is\nregistered/unregistered as observer. And the patch adds obd_putref()\nand obd_getref() into client_disconnect_export() not to call the\nfunction again in itself. (it's end up in a dead-lock of\ncli->cl_sem without it)\n\nSigned-off-by: Hiroya Nozaki <nozaki.hiroya@jp.fujitsu.com>\nChange-Id: Ib4d34c10d44b430e79a65ebdd7e4402e5f2c8c31\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b1_8"
    }
